Package: shapeshiftr
Title: Detecting Population Range Reconfiguration via Inter-individual Distances
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Nicola", "Love", , "nicolalove@zoology.ubc.ca", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A collection of tools to analyze shifts in the spatial cohesion of a group or population using inter-individual distances. Functions `cvpop`, `cvind`, and `cvratio` quantify variation in inter-individual distances and require only a matrix, two coordinate vectors, or a data frame with Cartesian coordinates (x and y as separate columns). The `iidist` function calculates inter-individual distances from an sf (simple features) object, producing output suitable for downstream analysis using `cvmetrics_sf`. 
